article.headline: Air Force 61, N.C. Central 49
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Grant Parker had 24 points and six rebounds as Air Force dealt North Carolina Central its fifth straight loss, winning 61-49 Wednesday night. Evan Washington scored a career-high 19 for Air Force (4-1), and Taylor Stewart added a season-high 13. The Falcons shot 58.5 percent. C.J. Wilkerson had 15 points for North Carolina Central (1-7). The Eagles, an independent team that will join the Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference on July 1, never led. North Carolina Central was outscored 40-22 in the paint.
